Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2073/92 of 30 June 1992 on promoting consumption in the Community and expanding the markets for milk and milk products (1), and in particular Article 4 thereof,
Whereas Article 6 (2) of Commission Regulation (EC) No 3582/93 (2) provides that the competent body shall conclude contracts for the selected measures with the successful applicants within one month of notification of the decision to the Member States; whereas this time limit expired on 2 June 1996 for the marketing year 1995/96; whereas strikes by the public services in Greece have precluded the conclusion of such contracts within the deadline for the marketing year 1995/96;
Whereas, as a result, a deadline of 31 December 1996 for the conclusion of the contract should be set for the marketing year 1995/96 in the case of Greece; whereas the delay in the conclusion of the contract will not necessitate a prolongation in the period for the accomplishment of the measures beyond the date that would otherwise have been applicable;
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Milk and Milk Products,
